x4freetext: The 2 MeV electrostatic generator. The deuteron beam
of about 1 microA  intensity and 1-2 keV energy
spread was focused onto the target after  magnetic
analysis. To check the bombarding energy the field of
the  deflecting magnet was measured by NMR.
The targets were self-supporting foils of 30-50
microg/cm2  thickness obtained by vacuum deposition
of carbon of  spectroscopic purity. The target
thickness of 17.6 keV theta  degree) was determined
by measuring the shift in the bombarding  energy of
the Ep=874 keV 19F(p,gamma) resonance.
